<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BOEHM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
You wouldn't think the comely, unclad figure on the cover needs a diet, but 
Wiedlin has to get off the sugar. 
</P>
<P>
Half of "Tangled" is slick and over-sweet. The former Go-Go does much better 
when setting her fragile, Cyndi Lauper sound-alike voice in more intimate 
ballad surroundings. Wiedlin also excels in two anthems that engage broad 
themes of war and freedom with emotional acuity. Why not make every song 
matter? MIKE BOEHM 
