<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: A LOOK AT UPCOMING EVENTS IN LOS ANGELES COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOXING AT THE BEACH: The Long Beach City Council will hold a hearing Tuesday on 
whether to give monthly boxing matches a permanent home at the Hyatt Regency. 
Patrons, mostly businessmen, have paid up to $50 to see professional bouts 
staged in the hotel's ballroom under a conditional use permit. 
</P>
<P>
* SCHOOL ELECTIONS: 107th Street School will hold elections for the 
Compensatory Education Advisory Council, the Bilingual Council and the School 
Site Council on Wednesday at 3 p.m. All members of the community are invited to 
attend. 
</P>
<P>
* FRINGE: The Fourth Annual Fringe of the Fringe Arts Festival starts Saturday 
in Claremont with a noon mask parade at Memorial Park in which artists create 
moving, noise-making sculptures. More than 100 events will be held from Pomona 
to Riverside and points between. The festival runs through Oct. 13. 
</P>
