<TEXT>
<P>
Jennifer Folsom, 29, whose husband committed suicide last June rather than 
watch her die of AIDS, which she contracted from a blood transfusion in 1979. 
Mrs. Folsom, whose 3-year-old daughter also has the disease, told her story in 
national interviews, saying she wanted to "live with dignity and not have 
people whispering behind (her) back." On Wednesday in Montpelier, Vt., of AIDS. 
