<HEADLINE>
<P>
29 TIED UP ON CORSICA, 2 BUNGALOWS BLOWN UP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
AJACCIO, Corsica 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Masked gunmen tied up 29 Italian vacationers and workers, then set off 
explosives that damaged two bungalows at a tourist complex being built in 
southern Corsica, police said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
There was no claim of responsibility, but the attack was similar to others 
claimed by guerrillas who seek Corsica's independence from France and oppose 
continuing tourist development on the Mediterranean island. 
</P>
</TEXT>
