<HEADLINE>
<P>
SITTING OUT 'DANCE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
What a disappointment! When I read Kirk Douglas' autobiography, "Ragman's Son," 
I was enormously impressed with this fine actor's ability as a writer. 
</P>
<P>
I looked forward to reading his recent book and first novel, "Dance With the 
Devil" (July 22). I should have saved my time and money. 
</P>
<P>
Recently, in a late-night TV interview, possibly defending his novel, Douglas 
said, "Well, you know there is more to my book than just raw sex." 
</P>
<P>
Not much, Mr. Douglas, not much. 
</P>
<P>
MERYL MEYERS 
</P>
<P>
LOS ANGELES 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA090990-0064 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 273462 </DOCID>
