152 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUTTAKES: MONSTER MASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By John M. Wilson 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gonzo journalist Dr. Hunter S. Thompson has replaced Morton Downey Jr. in "The 
Monster Tour," a "rock 'n roll horror comedy" scheduled to shoot in Atlanta 
late this fall. 
</P>
<P>
Downey, who dropped out to be a panelist on TV's revamped "To Tell the Truth," 
according to "Tour" producer Bill Reynolds . was to have played a record 
distributor. 
</P>
<P>
Angela Bowie, will portray the Fist Lady in the "wacky" feature about a 
heavy-metal group that wreaks havoc at a swank hotel after turning into such 
assorted creatures as were-wolves, Frankenstein, etc. 
</P>
<P>
L.A.-based rock group the Royal Court of China has signed up as the band. 
Director Hal Pierce in now courting comic Sam Kinison to play a second record 
distributor (Kinison is resisting). 
</P>
<P>
"They're a little controversial, like Angela Bowie," explains Reynolds of the 
casting choices. "It's a low-budget picture-we need all the publicity we can 
get." John M. Wilson 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA090990-0065 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 273463 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
September 9, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
