<HEADLINE>
<P>
AUTHOR, AUTHOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In Kari Granville's article "A Couple of Cops, With a Twist" (Sept. 2), 
producer Rob Cohen and director John Badham found this wonderful screenplay, 
"The Hard Way." And actor Michael J. Fox loved the unique story and actor James 
Woods thought the idea was fabulous, and throughout the article we learned all 
about Rob's and John's and Michael's and James' feelings and thoughts about 
this fantastic screenplay. 
</P>
<P>
Only one thing was left out of the article: Never once did anyone mention the 
name of the person who wrote this wonderful, fabulous, unique screenplay. 
</P>
<P>
I wonder what would happen if, suddenly, by some magic, the words on the script 
disappeared and Rob and John and Michael and James were left holding 120 blank 
pages. Would they be able to make their wonderful movie or would they be just 
sitting there quietly, with their fingers up their you-know-what? 
</P>
<P>
HOWARD ALBRECHT 
</P>
<P>
Sherman Oaks 
</P>
<P>
 A spokesman for the Badham/Cohen Group said that several people worked on the 
script and that the screenwriting credit has not been determined yet. 
</P>
<P>
