</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pope John Paul II, in Kabgayi, Rwanda, called for a narrowing of the gap 
between Africa's urban elite and rural poor and urged peasants in this 
infertile nation to redouble efforts to improve the quality of their lives. The 
pontiff said Rwandan peasants, who make up more than 80% of the population of 7 
million, have the right to demand the same health, social and administrative 
facilities, including credit banking, as their urban counterparts. 
