</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ousted Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto announced in Karachi that she will run in 
elections in October despite threats by caretaker rulers to have her 
disqualified. 
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for her Pakistan People's Party said Bhutto would run for three 
national assembly seats in her home province of Sind. Under Pakistani law, a 
candidate can seek more than one seat at a time but can keep only one 
afterwards. Special courts that can disqualify politicians from taking part in 
elections have already put some former government ministers on trial. 
</P>
