separated on the divided Korean peninsula be allowed to have temporary 
reunions. 
</P>
<P>
Kang said the exchanges could begin around Chusok, the Korean Thanksgiving Day, 
which falls on Oct. 3. It would be the second time that the hostile nations 
have allowed separated families to visit each other. There are about 10 million 
members of families separated by the division of the peninsula in 1945. 
</P>
