<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIG WEST ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
THIS TIME, FRESNO BEATS NEW MEXICO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fresno State avenged its only loss last season by defeating New Mexico, 24-17, 
Saturday night in a nonconference game at Fresno. 
</P>
<P>
New Mexico stunned the Bulldogs, 45-22, in Albuquerque at the end of last 
season. 
</P>
<P>
The Bulldogs (2-0) have won 18 consecutive games at home and have 20 victories 
in their last 21 games overall. 
</P>
<P>
Aaron Craver gained 175 yards in 31 carries and scored two touchdowns to lead 
Fresno. 
</P>
<P>
Quarterback Mark Barsotti completed 27 of 38 passes for career-high 301 yards 
and one touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
Craver scored on a 61-yard run early in the third quarter to give Fresno State 
a 17-14 lead and later scored on a one-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
Fresno State took a 7-0 lead on a 14-yard scoring pass from Barsotti to Marty 
Thompson in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
But New Mexico (0-1) led at halftime, 14-10. 
</P>
<P>
Pacific 41, CS Sacramento 33 -- Kris King passed for 289 yards and four 
touchdowns in leading the Tigers (1-1) at Stockton. 
</P>
<P>
Sacramento's Bobby Fresques, who passed for 329 yards and three touchdowns, was 
taken from the field by ambulance after being hit in the back with about 5 1/2 
minutes to play. He was hospitalized; the seriousness of his injury was not 
known. 
</P>
</TEXT>
