Cutter is in the front line, facing patients' frustration at long waits and the 
unavailability of many services, problems which only promise to escalate in the 
wake of funding cuts. The glass partition was erected to protect nurses from 
spitting patients and flying debris. ; Photo, Olive View's infusion room, 
above, is often so crowded that many cancer patients must be given chemotherapy 
in the hallway, below. ROLANDO OTERO / Los Angeles Times; Photo, Dr. Nancy 
