<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAFETY OF BICYCLISTS IS TWO-WAY STREET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re Richard Beene's commentary on bicycle safety: When I gave up motorcycles, my 
entire family had sighs of relief. 
</P>
<P>
Now we all participate in another life-threatening sport, but we are not going 
to quit. 
</P>
<P>
We find that the rewards outweigh the risks, which we reduced with proper 
bicycle maintenance, using helmets, practicing defensive riding and using 
designated bike lanes and paths whenever possible. 
</P>
<P>
The cyclist can make the difference. I, unfortunately, know all too well the 
alternatives to responsible cycling. 
</P>
<P>
CULLEN ELLINGBURGH 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Niguel 
</P>
</TEXT>
