<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO RUSHES PAST OCCIDENTAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Charles Taumoepeau gained 146 yards in 25 carries to lead the University of San 
Diego past Occidental, 20-12, before 4,000 in USD's Torero Stadium. It was the 
first Torero victory over Occidental since 1981. 
</P>
<P>
Freshman running back Brian Madlangbayan led the Tigers with 157 yards in 28 
carries, including 99 yards in nine first-quarter carries. 
</P>
<P>
Junior quarterback John Selle gave Occidental a 6-0 lead in the first quarter 
when he scored on a four-yard run around left end after a nice fake up the 
middle by Madlangbayan. 
</P>
<P>
Occidental's second touchdown came with 7 minutes 7 seconds left in the second 
quarter and gave the Tigers a 12-3 lead. Sophomore fullback Michael Winslow 
dived over from the one, capping a 10-play, 65-yard drive. 
</P>
<P>
All-American kicker Dave Bergmann kicked a 41-yard field goal to start the 
second half, giving USD a 13-12 lead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
