<P>
ANTELOPE VALLEY WINS OPENER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marty Washington passed for 165 yards and two touchdowns to lead visiting 
Antelope Valley College to a season-opening 22-15 victory over San Diego City 
on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Washington, a former redshirt at Grambling, completed 14 of 42 passes. 
</P>
<P>
Steve Miller rushed for 105 yards in 19 carries and David Brown and Chris 
Johnson caught scoring passes from Washington. 
</P>
<P>
The game ended in confusion. With the game clock broken, Antelope Valley let a 
free kick drop untouched. The Knights recovered and marched to the Antelope 
Valley 11-yard line before the officials declared the game over. 
</P>
