<HEADLINE>
<P>
HART'S DIXON RULED INELIGIBLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Billy Dixon, the top returnee from Hart High's Southern Section 3-A Division 
cross-country champion team, has been declared academically ineligible for the 
first month of the season. He could become eligible next month if he maintains 
a 2.0 grade-point average. 
</P>
<P>
"He realizes his mistakes and is trying his best to make up for them," Hart 
Coach Gene Blankenship said. I have no doubt he will be back and running in 
five weeks." 
</P>
<P>
Dixon, a senior who recorded marks of 4 minutes 23.4 seconds and 9:24.32 for 
1,600 and 3,200 meters in track last season, was Hart's second man on a team 
that advanced to the state Division I championships. 
</P>
<P>
Hart is ranked second in the preseason Southern Section Division II poll. 
</P>
