<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CRAIG ERNST 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fillmore 26, Pater Noster 0 -- Running backs Jon Alvarado and Val Pillado 
combined for 165 yards and three touchdowns to lead Fillmore past host Pater 
Noster. 
</P>
<P>
Pillado gained 87 yards in 14 carries and capped a seven-play drive late in the 
first quarter with a three-yard scoring run. 
</P>
<P>
After the ensuing kickoff, Fillmore stopped Pater Noster in four plays and set 
up a short drive that ended when Alvarado ran two yards for the first of his 
two touchdowns. His other touchdown came on a one-yard run late in the first 
half. 
</P>
<P>
Pater Noster quarterback Mike Avalos completed four of eight passes on the 
Eagles' next possession to push the ball to the Fillmore five-yard line. The 
drive was stopped when defensive back Steve Clinton made a diving interception 
in the end zone. 
</P>
<P>
Junior wide receiver Ray Garnica scored Fillmore's final touchdown on an 
eight-yard run on the final play of the third quarter. CRAIG ERNST 
</P>
</TEXT>
