<TEXT>
<P>
Our presence in Saudi Arabia is costing us a lot of money, obviously much more 
than we can readily afford. 
</P>
<P>
I have a suggestion as to who should pay the cost. It is Saddam Hussein. 
</P>
<P>
Iraq probably has $200 billion or more of assets that are available to us. The 
money we should use immediately for our daily expense, and other assets we 
should prepare to sell. 
</P>
<P>
We have been too good to the Iranians, and will probably, eventually, give back 
to them the billions we have seized. 
</P>
<P>
But it's time to get really tough with this ruffian. Make him understand that 
every day he postpones getting out of Kuwait, he is frittering away his assets. 
</P>
