<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; 
</P>
<P>
SHOPTALK; 
</P>
<P>
HOME ROMANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBIN TUCKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANYONE WHO SHOPS knows all about the phenomenal success of Laura Ashley's 
classic English designs. 
</P>
<P>
First there were the fashions, then the bolts of matching printed fabrics, wall 
coverings, linens and small home-furnishing items. The company was the first to 
introduce coordinated home furnishings at the consumer level. The 
home-furnishings line grew so popular it demanded its own showcase; thus, the 
Laura Ashley Home Store was born. 
</P>
<P>
The first branch in Southern California, a 2,640-square-foot South Coast Plaza 
store, features the entire range of Laura Ashley furnishings, presented, for 
inspiration, in room vignettes. 
</P>
<P>
Laura Ashley Home Store, South Coast Plaza, 3333 Bristol St., Costa Mesa; (714) 
545-9322. 
</P>
<P>
ROBIN TUCKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
