ENVIRONMENT: NOTES ABOUT YOUR SURROUNDINGS. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Raptor Attention -- Pete Bloom will give a slide presentation on California 
birds of prey at the next general meeting of the Sea and Sage Audubon Society, 
at 7:30 p.m. on Sept. 18. 
</P>
<P>
Bloom is a biologist specializing in birds of prey (raptors) and has worked on 
projects throughout California. He will discuss the status, habitat, migration 
patterns and identification of about 30 raptor species in California. 
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be held at Willard Intermediate School, 1342 N. Ross St., 
Santa Ana. Information: (714) 543-7393. 
</P>
<P>
Photo Finish -- The general meeting Wednesday of Amigos de Bolsa Chica will 
include a slide show featuring all entries in the group's fourth annual amateur 
photo contest. Winners will be announced after the show. The 7:30 p.m. meeting 
will be held in Room B7 of Huntington Beach City Hall, 2000 Main St. 
Information: (714) 897-7003. 
</P>
<P>
Marine Institute Potluck -- Nicholas Magalousis, director of the museum at 
Mission San Juan Capistrano, will discuss Native Americans and their 
relationship with the ocean at a meeting of the Orange County Marine Institute 
Volunteers on Wednesday. The public is invited to the 6 p.m. event at the 
Marine Institute, 24200 Dana Point Harbor Drive, Dana Point. Participants 
should bring table service and a dish that will serve eight. Information: Karen 
Arndt at (714) 496-2274. 
</P>
<P>
Beyond Recycling -- A public forum on waste-stream management will be held on 
Saturday at Rancho Santiago College, 17th and Bristol streets, Santa Ana. The 
event is sponsored by the League of Women Voters of Orange Coast. Five 
panelists will address the mounting crisis in landfill space. The forum will be 
held from 8:30 to 11:30 a.m. in Dunlap Hall. Information: (714) 548-9789. 
</P>
<P>
Volunteers Needed -- The second training session for volunteer naturalists at 
Upper Newport Bay Ecological Reserve begins soon. Help is needed with nature 
tours, office work, re-vegetation and other projects. Applications must be 
received by Friday. Information: (714) 640-6746. 
</P>
</TEXT>
