<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
TITAN MEN, UCLA WOMEN WIN CROSS-COUNTRY MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Fullerton cross-country team won the men's university division 
and finished fourth in the women's university division at the Titans' 
cross-country invitational Saturday at Carbon Canyon Park in Brea. UCLA won the 
women's division. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton's men were led by Steve Frisone, who finished fourth on the 
eight-kilometer course with a time of 25 minutes 43 seconds, Ray Tujillo (5th, 
25:59) and Mike Richardson (6th, 26:02). Shannon Winkleman of UC Riverside was 
first (25:22). 
</P>
<P>
Nicole Nucent of UCLA was first in the women's university division with a time 
of 18:27 on the five-kilometer course. 
</P>
<P>
Southern California College's Sherri Hall (18:37) won the women's college 
division. 
</P>
<P>
In the Cal State Fullerton women's volleyball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Long Beach 3, Cal State Fullerton 0 -- Cal State Long Beach (7-1) 
easily defeated Fullerton (3-5) in the consolation final, 15-2, 15-2, 15-1. 
Wisconsin won the championship by defeating Oregon State, 15-10, 9-15, 15-10, 
15-10. 
</P>
<P>
In the Whittier College women's volleyball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Southern California College 3, Azusa Pacific 1 -- Krista Hoover had 15 kills 
and was named to the all-tournament team and Heather Frewin has 10 kills to 
lead Southern California College (12-4) to a 12-15, 15-10, 15-8, 15-9, victory. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
UC Irvine 3, Oklahoma 0 -- Kim Collins had nine kills to lead host UC Irvine 
(2-3) to a 15-9, 15-6, 15-1 victory. 
</P>
<P>
Cal State San Bernardino 3, Christ College Irvine 1 -- Tammi Johnson had 15 
kills for host Christ College Irvine (3-8), which lost, 15-9, 15-13, 12-15, 
15-12. 
</P>
</TEXT>
