<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
VILLA PARK TAKES EARLY LEAD, BEATS BOLSA GRANDE, 43-21 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT JONES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Villa Park High School scored 30 points in the first half of a 43-21 victory 
over host Bolsa Grande. 
</P>
<P>
The Spartans scored first when Stanton Nielson recovered a blocked punt in the 
end zone to make the score 7-0. 
</P>
<P>
Bolsa Grande came back with a 12-play, 80-yard drive capped by Marcus Wilson's 
one-yard run which tied the score, 7-7. 
</P>
<P>
Ellis Williams' 90-yard touchdown run on the Spartans' first offensive play of 
the game gave Villa Park (1-0) a 14-7 lead with 5:02 minutes remaining in the 
first quarter. The Spartans, ranked No. 7 in Orange County, controlled the rest 
of the game as five players scored touchdowns. They led 30-7 at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Williams, a junior, paced the Villa Park offense by gaining 153 yards in 14 
carries. He also had an 88-yard kickoff return negated by a clipping penalty. 
SCOTT JONES 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
