<P>
Photo, Hot Wheels in South Gate: Employees of Imperial Tire Co. in South Gate 
try to salvage a tool chest from the smoldering wreckage of a two-alarm fire 
that destroyed eight installation bays and their contents of tires and rims 
early Wednesday morning. The fire, which closed Imperial Highway for several 
hours and pumped a plume of black smoke high into the air, slowed traffic on 
the Long Beach Freeway and caused an estimated $300,000 in damage. County fire 
investigators were trying to determine the cause of the blaze. The business, on 
Imperial Highway a few blocks east of the Long Beach Freeway, is owned by Dale 
Robertson of La Mirada. SARAH M. BROWN / For The Times 
</P>
