<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week: 
</P>
<P>
 Continue feeding chrysanthemums every three weeks until their buds show color. 
</P>
<P>
Remove dried up, faded flowers and replant containers and flower beds with more 
annuals to continue the color show well into fall. 
</P>
<P>
Because warm weather continues well into fall, be sure to maintain a regular 
watering schedule with deep, thorough soakings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
